14:
I-I'm not sure if these clothes suit
me...
33:
Wha—
Hey! You could at least pretend to
care!
37: I'm bored! I want new clothes too!
42:
Yeah, I don't blame you, but... They
don't sell kids' sizes here.
47:
You don't need new clothes right
now. Besides, you'll outgrow them
soon anyway.
54:
Excuse me... I could show you to
some nice accessories instead, if
you'd like.
74:
I'm sorry, I sh-should've picked a
different store...
79:
She's just being a kid. There's
nothing for you to apologize for.
82:
Honestly, you say sorry way too
much, you know that?
88: Scared? I'm not scared of you at all.
97:
I-I mean, not of your combat
abilities! You're not threatening
enough to make me nervous...
102:
Excuse me? Are you trying to make
me mad?!
107:
That's Phiria for you—honest to a
fault.
112:
It really isn't YOU that I'm scared of...
It's just... I can't stand the way things
are between us—
117:
You can't keep anything to yourself,
can you? Not that I have any idea
what you're going on about.
119:
What's with today, anyway? Inviting
us out to shop and all.
123:
I just thought... these clothes would
look cool on you...
128:
You're really telling me this whole
thing is about my sense of fashion?
136: Would you please be my friend?
149:
On behalf of the Farlands, I, Azrail
Swes, do hereby declare the
founding of our official partnership
with Palpebra!
151:
May our people walk together 
towards a brighter future!
154:
Azrail has really grown into his own.
The Swes family must be proud.
161:
Well, I, for one, am incredibly excited.
This should ease tensions between
Palpebra and the Farlands.
164:
Everyone has different aims, of
course. The Sweses will reap
economic benefits, while the
Sextans will have access to the
Academy.
167:
I don't see the Nouins involved
though.
170:
That's because the very capable Tris
family is here instead.
173:
Do you really think this partnership
means anything? If we're supposed
to be on good terms, why did we
bring so many soldiers?
177:
Perhaps your brother just wanted
his moment in the spotlight?
181:
Ciel looks the best when he's
swinging a blade though.
185:
You just like a good fight. Alk must
have his hands full when you're
around...
189:
Then why don't you spar with me
instead, Sir Nouin?
194:
To fight you, I'm afraid I'll need to
prepare quite a bit first—
202:
I see them! But it seems the soldiers
haven't!
206:
Well, Celtie, looks like you'll be
getting the fight you
wanted—against dragons of all
things!
